<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-01-16T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-01-16T21:00:00-05:00" n="5" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d5">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01 Manchuria/984: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-01-17T10:00:00+08:00">January 17, 1934—10
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received January 17—4:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>42. The following telegram has been received from the Consul General at
                            Harbin: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“January 16, 11 a.m. Japanese Consul General confirms report that
                                    Pu Yi will be made Emperor on March 1st.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>